(205, 1, '2019-06-18 19:16:59', '2019-06-18 19:16:59', '<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>If you fail knowledge Exam 3 times and you are under age of 18 years by law you must wait a full 15 days before you retake the exam .</li><li>if you fail the knowledge test three times ,you will not be able to take it fourth time until you have to complete an 8 hour course based on the Virginia drivers ,manual and approved by DMV This course is available at driving training school</li><li>student under age 18 if they have previously completed driver Ed class before taking course they should present certificate to school in order to take 8 hours class instead 36 hours</li><li>if customer fail 3 times in road skill test in DMV he has to take seven hours Reexamination class in order to take road test in DMV fourth time</li><li>Applicant age 18 or older must hold the learners permit for 60 days prior to first road skill test or complete a course of drivers education at a drivers training school approved by DMV or the department of education For applicant who choose to take drivers education ,the road skill teat will administered by the driver training school</li><li>According to Virginia law, if you are driving 20 or more miles per hour above the speed limit, or 81 miles per hour, a law enforcement officer may charge you with reckless driving IF convicted court may require a fine ,suspend your driving privilege and or impose jail sentence .</li><li>You must also stop if the school bus is loading or unloading passengers and the signals are not on.</li><li>when police, fire and rescue vehicles or ambulance approach you from behind using a siren flashing lights or both , you must immediately yield the right-of-way. Safely pull over to the right edge of the road and stop until emergency vehicle has passed .</li><li>State law requires motorist to pass cyclist at least 3 feet of clearance .</li><li>Use your low beam head lights in fog, rain and snow In fog light reflect back into your eyes.</li><li>Text messaging or reading of text messages while driving is illegal for all drivers.</li><li>Driver under age 18 are prohibited by va law from using cell phones or any other wireless communication device while driving .</li><li>Under Virginia law, the driver and all front seat passengers must wear safety belts.</li><li>All children under age 8 must be properly secured in a child safety seat when riding in vehicle</li><li>Children should ride rear facing from birth to 2 years.</li><li>If you break certain laws or repeatedly violates the laws of Virginia , your driving privilege may be suspend or revoked by the court and or DMV.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'DMV Laws', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dmv-laws', '', '', '2019-06-18 19:28:18', '2019-06-18 19:28:18', '', 0, 'http://localhost/eagle/?page_id=205', 0, 'page', '', 0),
